<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="521" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-08-03"><hi rend="italic">August 3,
                                1901</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Russell inquires if he can take charge of Colombian interests in
                            Venezuela in the event that the Colombian minister is given his
                            passport.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>